attributes.name: AI application
attributes.description: Specifies the function of AI in software, like predictive analytics or speech recognition

attributes.name: Additional animation software features
attributes.description: Specifies unique features in animation editing software, such as character animation or visual effects

attributes.name: Additional design software type
attributes.description: Specifies additional capabilities of design software, such as virtual tour or landscape design

attributes.name: Additional financial software features
attributes.description: Identifies extra capabilities of financial software, like asset management or auditing and compliance

attributes.name: Additional graphic software features
attributes.description: Highlights extra capabilities of graphic software, like digital illustration or layout design

attributes.name: Additional publishing software features
attributes.description: Highlights extra functionalities in publishing software, like print design or digital publishing

attributes.name: Additional security software features
attributes.description: Identifies extra capabilities of security software, e.g. disk encryption, intrusion detection

attributes.name: Artwork type
attributes.description: Specifies the style of digital artwork, such as typography or digital painting

attributes.name: Compatible programming languages
attributes.description: Identifies the programming languages a software product can work with, like Python or Java

attributes.name: Compatible software platform
attributes.description: Identifies the software platforms that a product is compatible with, such as Adobe Creative or Canva

attributes.name: Customer support channels
attributes.description: Specifies the ways customers can get help, such as phone support or video tutorials

attributes.name: Deployment type
attributes.description: Describes how AI software is implemented, such as hybrid or cloud-based

attributes.name: Disk format type
attributes.description: Identifies the type of disk format for software products, like Blu-ray or CD

attributes.name: ESRB rating
attributes.description: Identifies the age appropriateness of video games, such as E (Everyone) or T (Teen)

attributes.name: Education level
attributes.description: Specifies the educational stage the software is designed, such as elementary school or graduate school

attributes.name: Font style
attributes.description: Specifies the type of font in software products, such as sans serif or script

attributes.name: Footage type
attributes.description: Describes the category of stock photography or video footage, e.g. animations, textures

attributes.name: GPS software focus
attributes.description: Identifies the primary use of GPS software, such as automotive navigation or geospatial analysis

attributes.name: Icon type
attributes.description: Specifies the type of computer icon, such as folder or social media

attributes.name: Industry focus
attributes.description: Highlights the target sectors for a product, such as education or manufacturing

attributes.name: License type
attributes.description: Specifies the type of software license, such as open-source or one-time purchase

attributes.name: National/Regional rating
attributes.description: Specifies the national or regional rating for a video game, e.g. MA 15+, all ages

attributes.name: PEGI rating
attributes.description: Specifies the Pan European Game Information(PEGI) rating for video games, e.g. 3, 12

attributes.name: Performance metrics
attributes.description: Highlights key efficiency and effectiveness areas of AI and machine learning software, such as training time and inference speed

attributes.name: Primary region
attributes.description: Specifies the primary market or location for a software or cloud service, e.g. North America, Asia-Pacific

attributes.name: Service type
attributes.description: Identifies the category of cloud services, such as Platform as a service (PaaS) or Software as a service (SaaS)

attributes.name: Software features
attributes.description: Identifies the key functionalities of a software product, such as privacy protection or auto backup

attributes.name: Software tool type
attributes.description: Classifies the type of software development tools, like source code editor or version control system

attributes.name: Template type
attributes.description: Specifies the category of document templates, e.g. business card, flyer

attributes.name: Training data requirements
attributes.description: Identifies the data type and quality needed for effective AI or machine learning software training, e.g. labeled data

attributes.name: User type
attributes.description: Identifies the intended user of a software product, such as individual or small business

attributes.name: Utility/Maintenance task type
attributes.description: Categorizes the task performed by a software, such as disk cleanup or system optimizer

attributes.name: Video game content features
attributes.description: Identifies special features of video game software, e.g. downloadable content (DLC), early access

attributes.name: Video game format
attributes.description: Specifies the method of delivery and type of media for video games, such as digital or physical.

attributes.name: Video game sub-genre
attributes.description: Identifies the specific subcategory of a video game, like MMORPG or battle royale

attributes.name: Wallpaper theme
attributes.description: Identifies the main subject or style of a desktop wallpaper, such as nature or abstract
